554637	eng	Everyone is entitled to all the rights and freedoms set forth in this Declaration, without distinction of any kind, such as race, colour, sex, language, religion, political or other opinion, national or social origin, property, birth or other status.	jakov	2010-10-09 15:31:38	2010-10-09 15:31:38
