3952186	eng	American and Russian scientists utilized animals - mainly monkeys, chimps and dogs - in order to test each country's ability to launch a living organism into space and bring it back alive and unharmed.	Hybrid	2015-03-13 04:29:35	2015-03-13 04:29:35
3952196	eng	On December 12, 1949, the last V-2 monkey flight was launched at White Sands. Albert IV, a rhesus monkey attached to monitoring instruments, was the payload. It was a successful flight, with no ill effects on the monkey until impact, when it died.	Hybrid	2015-03-13 04:33:35	2015-03-13 04:33:35
