5177439	eng	Through both denotation and connotation, many Turkish names are weighty with symbolism. Before the Second World War, the European system of name-giving was adopted, and the people of Turkey chose new surnames for themselves from a list of names which had been created on the basis of etymology and semantics.	Objectivesea	2016-05-31 01:25:30	2016-05-31 01:25:30
