6708735	eng	Lake Erie is known for seiches, especially when strong winds blow from southwest to northeast. In 1844, a 22-foot seiche breached a 14-foot-high sea wall killing 78 people and damming the ice to the extent that Niagara Falls temporarily stopped flowing.	Hybrid	2018-02-24 16:30:41	2018-02-24 16:30:41
