7880122	eng	The chief baker seeing that he had wisely interpreted the dream, said: I also dreamed a dream, that I had three baskets of meal upon my head: And that in one basket which was uppermost, I carried all meats that are made by the art of baking, and that the birds ate out of it.	carlosalberto	2019-04-30 18:34:59	2019-04-30 18:34:59
