7885902	eng	Due to the regularity of the language, speaking Esperanto gives you the feeling of driving on a freeway because all hindrances have been removed. Grammatical exceptions in national languages act like stop signs on the brain and make you feel that you're driving in city traffic.	Dejo	2019-05-03 15:29:53	2019-05-03 15:29:53
